The seminar consists of two parts. In spring term you will learn how to present the results of your research in both the scientific and popular form, how to prepare poster and oral presentations and how to write an article. The seminars in autumn term are based on texts analysis. Joint discussions of the students' research topics will take place.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The objective of the course is to give an overview of the communication in science and to provide knowledge of basic concepts of archaeological research themes.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  After completing the course, the student has knowledge of science communication and science popularization, and is familiar with the basic concepts of archaeological research themes.
